        "creation_date": 1533541031,
        "answer_count": 1,
        "title": "Exclude Jhipster and upgrade Spring Boot from 1.4.0 to 2.0.3",
        "body": "<p>I am using spring boot 1.4.0 along with jhipster 3.6.1 in my project. I want to upgrade spring boot from 1.4.0 to 2.0.3 but I found some release notes of jhipster according to which it won't support Spring boot 2.0.3.<\/p>\n\n<p>Can anyone help me out by letting me know if there is any easy and quick way to exclude jhipster from my project.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 51702671,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "angularjs",
            "spring",
            "spring-boot",
            "jhipster"
        ],
        "score": 1,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 1162,
        "last_edit_date": 1533545489
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/Cc397.jpg?s=256",
            "account_id": 33534,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 93960,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/93960/ga%c3%abl-marziou",
            "reputation": 16344,
            "display_name": "Ga&#235;l Marziou"
        },
        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
        "score": 1,
        "is_accepted": false,
        "last_activity_date": 1533544637,
        "creation_date": 1533544273,
        "body": "<p>JHipster 3 won't be updated for Spring Boot 2, only JHipster 5 supports it.<\/p>\n\n<p>So either you upgrade your project to JHipster 5 using <code>jhipster upgrade<\/code> command or you remove all dependencies from JHipster and you manually upgrade your project.<\/p>\n\n<p>These dependencies can be of 3 types: BOM for maven dependencies, server library and client library (not required for your use case). For <a href=\"https://github.com/jhipster/jhipster\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">BOM and server library<\/a>, the idea is to retrieve the source of the version used by your app and to integrate it into your own git repo so that you can modify it.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 51703498,
        "question_id": 51702671,
        "last_edit_date": 1533544637
    }],
